MENDOTA HILLS, LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Mendota Hills, LLC ("Mendota Hills") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Mendota Hills generating facility ("Mendota Hills Facility").
The Mendota Hills Facility is a wind turbine generating facility located in Lee County, Illinois. The Mendota Hills Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by Commonwealth Edison Company of Illinois and under the operational control of the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Mendota Hills' revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Mendota Hills Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Mendota Hills' monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Mendota Hills shall be subject to Schedule 2 of PJM's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $288,000.00 The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $24,000.00
